{"first_name":"Shelby","last_name":"Bonnie","permalink":"shelby-bonnie","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/shelby-bonnie","homepage_url":"http://whiskeymedia.com","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"shelbybonnie","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"CNET Networks","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Thu Nov 22 08:36:57 UTC 2007","updated_at":"Fri Sep 25 19:03:42 UTC 2009","overview":"<p>Shelby Bonnie is CEO of <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/whiskey-media\" title=\"Whiskey Media\">Whiskey Media</a>, an online publisher that builds topical Websites, including giantbomb.com, comicvine.com and animevice.com.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to Whiskey Media, he co-founded <a href=\"http://www.crunchbase.com/company/cnetnetworks\" title=\"CNET\">CNET</a> in 1993 with Halsey Minor.  He resigned from the positions of chairman and CEO in October 2006 following a <a href=\"http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2006/10/12/CNET.TMP\" title=\"stock options backdating scandal\" rel=\"nofollow\">stock options backdating scandal</a> that took place between 1996 and 2003. He was later <a href=\"http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1015577/000119312507195139/d8k.htm\" title=\"completely exonerated\" rel=\"nofollow\">completely exonerated</a> and continued to serve as  director of CNET Networks until March 2007.</p>\n\n<p>Before CNET, Bonnie worked for Tiger Management Corporation, Lynx Capital, and Morgan Stanley.</p>\n\n<p>He received a BS in Commerce from the University of Virginia and an MBA from Harvard Business School.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,122],"assets/images/resized/0001/5979/15979v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[240,196],"assets/images/resized/0001/5979/15979v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[240,196],"assets/images/resized/0001/5979/15979v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"MBA","subject":"","institution":"Harvard Business School","graduated_year":n